The Narok county government yesterday demolished illegal kiosks as part of measures to mitigate flash floods during heavy rains. In a seven-day notice issued by the Physical Planning and Urban Development department, the orders said the structures were built along waterways and road reserves. Read more : Narok traders incur Sh20m losses as floods drown stock, disrupt transport In a letter by chief officer Justus Rutto dated November 21, the kiosk owners were told to remove the kiosks, or they would be taken down. “Kiosks have tremendously mushroomed in Narok town. All kiosk operators are directed to demolish them forthwith from the date of this letter, failing which the county will demolish them,” reads part of the letter. At the weekend, the town was hit by flash floods that destroyed property worth millions of shillings. Click here fore more political news 